nce-policy/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Flexible Working</title><link>/docs/handbook/03_employee_resources/employee_handbook/3.-time--attendance/work-arrangements/flexible-working/</link><pubDate>Thu, 01 May 2025 21:06:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/docs/handbook/03_employee_resources/employee_handbook/3.-time--attendance/work-arrangements/flexible-working/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="flexible-working-policy">Flexible Working Policy&lt;/h1>
&lt;h2 id="1-purpose-and-scope">1. Purpose and Scope&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>This policy outlines our approach to flexible working arrangements and applies to all employees of Green Orbit Digital.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="2-definition-of-flexible-working">2. Definition of Flexible Working&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Flexible working arrangements may include:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>Remote working (working from home or another location)&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>Flexible hours (varying start and finish times)&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>Compressed work weeks&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>Part-time arrangements&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>Job sharing&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 id="3-eligibility">3. Eligibility&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>All employees who have completed their probationary period are eligible to request flexible working arrangements. Approval will be based on:&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Flexitime Policy</title><link>/docs/handbook/03_employee_resources/employee_handbook/3.-time--attendance/work-arrangements/flexitime-policy/</link><pubDate>Thu, 01 May 2025 21:06:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/docs/handbook/03_employee_resources/employee_handbook/3.-time--attendance/work-arrangements/flexitime-policy/</guid><description>&lt;ol>
&lt;li>Introduction&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;p>At Green Orbit Digital, we value the well-being and work-life balance of our employees. We understand that everyone has unique scheduling needs and responsibilities outside of work. Therefore, we offer a flexitime policy to provide flexibility in work hours while ensuring that business needs are met.&lt;/p>
&lt;ol start="2">
&lt;li>Eligibility&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;p>All full-time employees of Green Orbit Digital are eligible to participate in the flexitime program. Part-time employees may also be considered for flexible working arrangements based on their role and workload.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Mobile And Remote Access Policy</title><link>/docs/handbook/03_employee_resources/employee_handbook/3.-time--attendance/work-arrangements/mobile-and-remote-access-policy/</link><pubDate>Thu, 01 May 2025 21:06:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/docs/handbook/03_employee_resources/employee_handbook/3.-time--attendance/work-arrangements/mobile-and-remote-access-policy/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Overtime Policy</title><link>/docs/handbook/03_employee_resources/employee_handbook/3.-time--attendance/work-arrangements/overtime-policy/</link><pubDate>Thu, 01 May 2025 21:06:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/docs/handbook/03_employee_resources/employee_handbook/3.-time--attendance/work-arrangements/overtime-policy/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Remote And Agile Working</title><link>/docs/handbook/03_employee_resources/employee_handbook/3.-time--attendance/work-arrangements/remote-and-agile-working/</link><pubDate>Thu, 01 May 2025 21:06:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/docs/handbook/03_employee_resources/employee_handbook/3.-time--attendance/work-arrangements/remote-and-agile-working/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Remote Work &amp; Byod Policy</title><link>/docs/handbook/03_employee_resources/employee_handbook/3.-time--attendance/work-arrangements/remote-work--byod-policy/</link><pubDate>Thu, 01 May 2025 21:06:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/docs/handbook/03_employee_resources/employee_handbook/3.-time--attendance/work-arrangements/remote-work--byod-policy/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Remote Working And Homeworking Policy</title><link>/docs/handbook/03_employee_resources/employee_handbook/3.-time--attendance/work-arrangements/remote-working-and-homeworking-policy/</link><pubDate>Thu, 01 May 2025 21:06:00 +0000</